receptor pairs is produced during T cell activation to promote clonal expansion?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Interleukin-1 and IL-1R","Interleukin-2 and IL-2R","Interleukin-3 and IL-3R","Interleukin-7 and IL-7R","Interleukin-6 and IL-6R"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EFollowing T cell activation, \u003Cstrong\u003EInterleukin-2\u003C/strong\u003E and its receptor (IL-2R) are specifically upregulated. This creates an autocrine signaling loop that drives T cell proliferation and differentiation, leading to clonal expansion of antigen-specific T cells.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EInterleukin-1\u003C/strong\u003E is primarily produced by macrophages and dendritic cells to promote inflammation. \u003Cstrong\u003EInterleukin-3\u003C/strong\u003E supports haematopoiesis and is not specifically involved in T cell activation. \u003Cstrong\u003EInterleukin-7\u003C/strong\u003E is important for lymphoid development and homeostasis but is produced by stromal cells, not T cells. \u003Cstrong\u003EInterleukin-6\u003C/strong\u003E is mainly produced by macrophages and promotes acute phase responses.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe IL-2/IL-2R pathway represents a critical positive feedback mechanism that amplifies the T cell response following initial activation.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Interleukin-2 (IL-2) and its receptor IL-2R are produced during T cell activation and are essential for T cell proliferation and differentiation.","IL-2 is a key cytokine that promotes T cell clonal expansion through autocrine signaling.","The IL-2/IL-2R pathway represents a critical positive feedback loop in T cell activation."],"references":["Ross SH, Cantrell DA. Signaling and Function of Interleukin-2 in T Lymphocytes. Annu Rev Immunol. 2018 Apr 26;36:411-433. doi: 10.1146/annurev-immunol-042617-053352. PMID: 29677473; PMCID: PMC6472684.","Esensten JH, Helou YA, Chopra G, Weiss A, Bluestone JA. CD28 Costimulation: From Mechanism to Therapy. Immunity. 2016 May 17;44(5):973-88. doi: 10.1016/j.immuni.2016.04.020. PMID: 27192564; PMCID: PMC4932896","Bona, C. A., \u0026 Bonilla, F. A. (2019). Textbook of immunology. CRC press","Kumar, V., Abbas, A. K., \u0026 Aster, J. C. (Eds.). (2012). Robbins basic pathology e-book. Elsevier Health Sciences."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"97447"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"14990"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"97447","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/97447"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-09-23T18:31:43+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-09-23T18:31:58+09:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7678"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"115444"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"7"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"4908","links":